@alex-cory The `fingerprint` property is only available when you create the token with a secret API key and never with the publishable key. This was released in the API version [2014-10-07](https://stripe.com/docs/upgrades#2014-10-07):

> Publishable keys can no longer be used to retrieve token objects. When a card or bank account token is created with a publishable key, the fingerprint property is no longer included in the response.

Our example uses a Secret API key to crete and retrieve the token which is why you're seeing it in the docs.

