Is there any particular reason why a graph cut would out perform the DP approach in the [original paper](http://www.win.tue.nl/~wstahw/edu/2IV05/seamcarving.pdf) ?

The original approach just required one operation (a bunch of comparisons and additions) per pixel, for each seam removal. Won't the graph cut approach require a reconstruction of the graph after removing a single seam ?

