It's not a hard limit in the sense that if you update an entity group twice in a single second that one of the requests will necessarily fail. But if you are updating an entity group on average more than once per second, it may lead to performance issues.

If the `Person` entities in your example are each in their own entity group:

Bob entity:
```
{
  "key": 
  {
    "path": 
    [
      {
        "kind": "Person",
        "id": "1"
      }
    ]
  },
  "properties": 
  {
    "name": 
    {
      "stringValue": "Bob"
    }
  }
}
```

Sally entity:
```
{
  "key": 
  {
    "path": 
    [
      {
        "kind": "Person",
        "id": "2"
      }
    ]
  },
  "properties": 
  {
    "name": 
    {
      "stringValue": "Sally"
    }
  }
}
```

then you can update each of them once per second.

We'd love to improve the docs on this. Can you let us know where you were reading about the update limit?

